name: Flag of Transnistria
description: The flag of Transnistria features three horizontal stripes: red, green, and red. Transnistria is a self-proclaimed republic located in Eastern Europe, primarily on the east bank of the Dniester River. The region is known for its Russian-speaking population, Soviet-era symbols, and ongoing political discussions regarding its status.

name: Flag of the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
description: The flag of the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia featured a plain red background with a centrally positioned blue-bordered white star, symbolizing socialist unity. The federation existed from 1945 until its dissolution in the early 1990s due to economic challenges, political instability, ethnic tensions, and the collapse of communism in Eastern Europe. Slovenia, Croatia, and later Bosnia and Herzegovina declared independence, leading to armed conflicts from 1991 to 1995.
